   "regular-body" : "<p><a href=\"http://eternalfarnham.tumblr.com/post/156827299361/val-tashoth-val-tashoth-robes-are-stupid-my\" class=\"tumblr_blog\">eternalfarnham</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"http://val-tashoth.tumblr.com/post/156770867433/val-tashoth-robes-are-stupid-my-sorcerer-dresses\" class=\"tumblr_blog\">val-tashoth</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"http://val-tashoth.tumblr.com/post/156768936783/robes-are-stupid-my-sorcerer-dresses-like-petyr\" class=\"tumblr_blog\">val-tashoth</a>:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Robes are stupid. My sorcerer dresses like Petyr Baelish.</p></blockquote>\n<p>To expand: if you are a mage, dress like a noble. Do not dress like a wizard. Pointy conical hat and sky-blue robes is medieval semaphore forÂ âkill first and with extreme prejudice.â Tailored black silk over cloth-of-gold and studded with rubies saysÂ âHarmless, but valuable; ransom if possible or kill last.âÂ </p>\n<p>If you dress like a noble, theyâre not going to pay attention as you take a turn or two to back away from the melee and prepare yourself. The ruse is only broken when you reveal yourself, at which point 8d6 fire damage is screaming toward them at Mach Fuck anyway, so no big.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>counterpoint: if you donât get to dress like someone ran a magical thrift shop through a rototiller and frankensteined the pieces back together whatâs the god-damned point of being a wizard</p>\n</blockquote>",
